      <title>Re: Alternatives to hacking core?</title>
      <link>http://projects.ez.no/enhancedezbinaryfile/forum/general/alternatives_to_hacking_core/re_alternatives_to_hacking_core8</link>
      <description>Hmm... I'm not sure I'm understanding this 100%: &#13;
&#13;
you want an object created with at least two attributes - a comment and a link to a file object (I assume a text line for a name too).&#13;
&#13;
Anonymous users should not be able to read the comment but they should be able to get the link to download the file.&#13;
&#13;
Admin user(s) should be notified when someone creates this object.&#13;
&#13;
I'm assuming the file should be permanent with a link in the ezbinaryfile table.&#13;
&#13;
You have access to the roles.&#13;
&#13;
You do not have access to the kernel.&#13;
 &#13;
If the above is all true then I think the edit functionality is probably better to use since the file is then its own object and is in the ezbinary file.  If the file should be temporary then the collection functionality using this extension is better (but not the kernel hack).&#13;
&#13;
The comment attribute can easily be hidden with an if "is_logged_in" statement around the attribute in the front-end view template for the object class.&#13;
&#13;
The notification can probably be done using the notification system (assuming the crons are set up etc.)&#13;
&#13;
If it can't be done with the notifications because the crons won't be set up... or there is something else that won't work because of the setup there, then you can always go with a completely custom extension - which could create an object, set it to hidden or set it to a section that can be controlled with roles, and upload the file, set it in the ezbinaryfile table and send emails to whomever.  It's not a particularly hard extension to do.&#13;
&#13;
If that's the way you want to go and you don't have that skill-set internally and need more assistance then contact me through my website ( http://www.leidentech.com ) or take a look at some of the other companies in the http://share.ez.no/index.php/members-partners/find-a-partner index.</description>
