      <title>Re: Alternatives to hacking core?</title>
      <link>http://projects.ez.no/enhancedezbinaryfile/forum/general/alternatives_to_hacking_core/re_alternatives_to_hacking_core6</link>
      <description>"external visitors, people without an account or any access to site administration" - that's the Anonymous user - and if you want comments to be created by Anonymous users you can set Anonymous-&gt;content create-&gt;class comment in the roles - and then you should be able to have anonymous users create a comment.  If you the add a file attribute to the comment class and add that to your comment edit templates then they should be able to upload a file using the standard "edit" functionality and not the "collection" functionality.&#13;
&#13;
I think that's what you want.  Or, at the very least that's the ezpublish way of doing comments.  It doesn't make sense to use the information collection process since you are already creating a "comment" object (with the edit functionality) so you won't have an information collection object. &#13;
&#13;
There are still - perhaps - reasons to use the information collection process... but if you can come up with a reason I can probably come up with the better way for the same functionality without using the information collection process.  Of course if you are &lt;i&gt;bound&lt;/i&gt; to using the information collection process for whatever political bs internal reason then this extension can probably be easily modified to easily ge the file path information. &#13;
&#13;
 &#13;
&#13;
</description>
