    <item>
      <title>Re: Alternatives to hacking core?</title>
      <link>http://projects.ez.no/enhancedezbinaryfile/forum/general/alternatives_to_hacking_core/re_alternatives_to_hacking_core4</link>
      <description>Here is a snippet of code that I used to create a file - the part that does it is the $dataType-&gt;insertRegularFile - this might help you narrow down what you want to look for:&#13;
&#13;
&lt;code&gt;&#13;
if (count($errors) == 0 AND $_FILES['file']['size'] &gt; 0 ) {&#13;
        if (!file_exists($targetDir))&#13;
                @mkdir($targetDir,0775, true);&#13;
        // Clean the fileName for security reasons&#13;
        $fileName = preg_replace('/[^\w\._]+/', '', $_FILES['file']['name']);&#13;
        // Read binary input stream and append it to temp file&#13;
        $content = file_get_contents($_FILES['file']['tmp_name']);&#13;
        file_put_contents( $targetDir . DIRECTORY_SEPARATOR . $fileName, $content);&#13;
        $upload = $dataType-&gt;insertRegularFile( $editObject, $version, $language, $attribute,$targetDir . DIRECTORY_SEPARATOR . $fileName, &$result );&#13;
        @unlink($targetDir . DIRECTORY_SEPARATOR . $fileName);&#13;
&#13;
        if ($upload != TRUE) {&#13;
                $errors[] = ezpI18n::tr( 'design/gbw', "Upload failed");&#13;
        }&#13;
        if($result['errors']) {&#13;
                $errors = array_merge($errors,$result['errors']);&#13;
        }&#13;
}&#13;
&lt;/code&gt;</description>
      <author>community@ez.no (Steven E Bailey)</author>
