    <item>
      <title>Re: Alternatives to hacking core?</title>
      <link>http://projects.ez.no/enhancedezbinaryfile/forum/general/alternatives_to_hacking_core/re_alternatives_to_hacking_core3</link>
      <description>Actually, the kernel hack is only to add the file to the notification email - so you can can get away with not using that in your case...&#13;
&#13;
The problem though is that the information for the file is stored in the ezinfocollection_attribute table as xml - with an entry to the location of the file in the var directory (something like this: &lt;siteaccess&gt;/storage/original/attachments/application/5a5ae635ec635f65dccbb0b184c11944.pdf) and the original filename not in the binary file table.   The content download link is what returns the hash file from the direct hash link with the current filename.&#13;
&#13;
It would actually make more sense (to me) to use the existing file upload functionality (which can be seen with multifileupload and the plupload extensions) instead of the collected information - is there a reason why you are using the collected information functionality?&#13;
&#13;
The more I think about this the more I think it "could" work with some modifications maybe, but it's not really the best way to go.&#13;
&#13;
 </description>
      <author>community@ez.no (Steven E Bailey)</author>
